.TH "DOTTY" "1" "Jun 2026" "Auto generated by spf13/cobra" ""

.SH NAME
dotty-dotfiles-restore - Copy a backup set back over the links that displaced it.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdotty dotfiles restore [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Restore the files a link run backed up: every file in the chosen backup set
is copied back to the absolute path it came from, replacing the symlink that
displaced it. Without --timestamp, an interactive picklist offers the
available sets, newest first. The set is copied, not consumed — a restore can
be repeated.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for restore

.PP
\fB--timestamp\fP=""
	backup set to restore (a directory name under the backups dir)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--profile\fP=""
	profile to operate on (defaults to the active profile)

.PP
\fB--repo\fP=""
	dotfiles repository (default: found via $REPOS_DIR)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  dotty dotfiles restore
  dotty dotfiles restore --timestamp=2026-07-15T10-30-00
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBdotty-dotfiles(1)\fP
